          ],
          "INC-SPECT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "From measurement of the fast/thermal -neutron flux",
                "ratio for monitor reactions having different threshold",
                "it was concluded that the neutron spectrum used was",
                "approximately a fission spectrum."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "REAC"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " On the average the fast neutron flux density",
                " was 7x10**13/cm2/s."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV",
                "GSPEC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Cross sections were measured by neutron",
                "activation of the target nuclei and the radioactive",
                "products were identified by gamma-ray spectrometry."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "CHSEP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "Each cross-section value is a mean of at least six",
                "independent measurements."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The radioactivity of the reaction products and",
                "the monitor reactions was detennined by gamma-ray",
                "spectrometry using a co-axial 270 cm3 HPGe detector in",
                "conjunction with a 4K Canberra Series 85 multichannel",
                "analyzer."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "PART-DET": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "DG"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "In converting the count rates to decay rates correc-",
                "tions were applied for radiochemical yields, gamma-ray",
                "intensities, detector efficiencies, counting geometry,",
                "absorption, self-absorption, pile-up effects and",
                "coincidence losses."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-T",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The given uncertainties incorporate both",
                "statistical and systematic uncertainties.",
                "The main sources of uncertainties involved in",
                "cross-section measurements were those associated with",
                "the determination of fast neutron flux densities (<8%)",
                "and absolute decay rates (5 to 10%).",
                "Other sources of uncertainties were small and were due",
                "to uncertainties in the number of target nuclei (< 1%)",
                "as well as in irradiation and cooling times (<<1%).",
                "The overall uncertainty in each reaction cross section",
                "was obtained by summing the individual uncertainties",
                "in quadrature."
              ]
            }
          ],
